# XUID Entity Identifiers

All entities in Prism use **XUIDs** (URL-friendly compressed UUIDs from [linkorb/xuid](https://github.com/linkorb/xuid)) as their public identifier. Internal auto-increment IDs are never exposed in URLs, MCP tool inputs/outputs, or API responses.

## Required Pattern

Every entity MUST:

1. Have a `xuid` column (VARCHAR 22, unique, indexed)
2. Generate the XUID in the constructor via `Xuid::getXuid()`
3. Expose `getXuid()` but **not** `getId()` in public-facing interfaces

```php
use Xuid\Xuid;

#[ORM\Column(length: 22, unique: true)]
private string $xuid;

public function __construct(...)
{
    $this->xuid = Xuid::getXuid();
}
```

## Where XUIDs Are Used

| Context | Use XUID | Use internal ID |
|---|---|---|
| URLs (admin routes) | Yes | Never |
| MCP tool input/output | Yes | Never |
| `toArray()` / API responses | Yes | Never |
| Doctrine relations (FK) | No (use internal ID) | Yes |
| Repository queries (internal) | Either | Either |

## Repository Pattern

Repositories should have a `findOneByXuid()` method and server-scoped variants:

```php
public function findOneByServerAndXuid(string $serverName, string $xuid): ?Node
{
    return $this->createQueryBuilder('n')
        ->andWhere('n.serverName = :server')
        ->andWhere('n.xuid = :xuid')
        ->setParameter('server', $serverName)
        ->setParameter('xuid', $xuid)
        ->getQuery()
        ->getOneOrNullResult();
}
```

## Why

- XUIDs are unguessable (no sequential IDs in URLs)
- Shorter than UUIDs (22 chars vs 36)
- URL-safe without encoding
- Decouple public identifiers from database internals
